## 2. Per-task workflow (do this every time, no shortcuts)

1. `gid_update_task(graph_path=<v03 db>, id=<task_id>, status="in_progress")`
2. Read the task node — get description + cited §-numbers + cited GOAL/GUARD ids
3. Open `.gid/features/<feature>/design.md`, read the cited §s
4. Open `.gid/features/<feature>/requirements.md`, read the cited GOAL/GUARDs
5. Read 1-2 sibling files in the same module for style
6. Implement
7. `cargo test -p engramai --lib` (or `-p engram-bench` for bench tasks) — must be green
8. Commit (Conventional Commits, ref task ID)
9. `gid_complete(graph_path=<v03 db>, id=<task_id>)` — note the unblocked downstream tasks
10. Move to next ready task

**Never mark a task done if (a) tests fail OR (b) the target file doesn't exist on disk.**

