# §E — Stop conditions, status reporting, escalation

## When to stop and write STATUS

Write `tasks/2026-04-27-night-autopilot-STATUS.md` and STOP if any of:

1. A previously-green test goes red and 2 fix attempts fail
2. A task description references a file or section that doesn't exist (e.g., design §X.Y not found)
3. You'd need to make a non-trivial design decision not pinned in design.md
4. Cross-feature contract conflict (e.g., `ResolutionStats` field doesn't match what bench expects)
5. v0.3 graph DB integrity looks off (unexpected snapshot files, edge-count drift, gid_validate failures)
6. `cargo build` breaks at the workspace level (not just the crate you're editing)
7. You hit a §C migration test failure — STOP IMMEDIATELY, migration bugs corrupt user data

## Status file format

```markdown
# Autopilot Status — 2026-04-27 night

## Completed
- task:res-impl-memory-api  ✅ commit abc123
- task:res-impl-knowledge-compile  ✅ commit def456
- ...

